#ROOM
Vnum     13020
Name     &dRoland's Doom&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     The hills here are riddled with abandoned mine shafts. The area has been
completely taken over by the Nightbane Worgen. These ferocious beastmen
leap from the shadows with razor-sharp claws.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    13019
Desc      The Gloomy Path.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13021
Desc      An open mine shaft.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13010 2 13020
  Reset G 1 13008 10
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13021
Name     &dRoland's Doom - The Mine&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    dark indoors~
Desc     The timber supports of this mine are rotting away. The Worgen use these
tunnels as a den, their terrifying howls echoing off the stone walls.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13020
Desc      The hills outside.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13010 2 13021
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13022
Name     &dVul'Gol Ogre Mound - Entrance&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     A massive, crude mound of dirt and logs rises from the southern woods.
It is home to the brutish Vul'Gol ogres. The smell of unwashed bodies
and roasting meat is incredibly strong.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13023
Desc      The Darkened Road East.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13023
Name     &dThe Darkened Road - East&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     Leaving Darkshire to the east, the road becomes even more treacherous.
The fog clings to the ground, hiding the roots and rocks. Stitches the
Abomination is known to march down this road on his path of destruction.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    13000
Desc      Darkshire Town Square.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    13029
Desc      The road to Deadwind Pass.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13022
Desc      The Ogre Mound.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13024
Desc      Brightwood Grove.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13024
Name     &dBrightwood Grove&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     Despite its name, there is nothing bright about this grove. It is heavily
infested with Nightbane Worgen who stalk the perimeter of Darkshire,
waiting for the Night Watch to drop their guard.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13023
Desc      The eastern road.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13025
Desc      Deeper into the grove.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13010 2 13024
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13025
Name     &dBrightwood Grove - Deep Woods&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     The Worgen are relentless here. The trees are heavily scarred by massive
claw marks, and the undergrowth is trampled down by pack hunting. To the
north, a faint, pure light glows through the fog.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13024
Desc      The edge of the grove.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13026
Desc      Twilight Grove.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13010 3 13025
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13026
Name     &dTwilight Grove - Approach&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     The fog suddenly lifts. The trees here are ancient and incredibly tall,
their leaves a vibrant, glowing green. A pristine sanctuary hidden within
the cursed woods, protected by ancient magic.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13025
Desc      Brightwood Grove.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13027
Desc      The Moonwell.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13027
Name     &dTwilight Grove - The Moonwell&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     A massive, glowing Moonwell sits in the center of a crater. A colossal
tree with a portal in its roots towers above it, connecting to the
Emerald Dream. The air is perfectly calm and pure.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13026
Desc      The grove approach.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13028
Name     &dBeggar's Haunt&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     A lonely, ruined tower sits on a hill near the eastern border. It is a
place of dark rumors and ghost stories, avoided by the locals.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13029
Desc      The road to Deadwind Pass.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

